description:
&lt;p&gt;Secure Care regional and national service offering care and treatment to individuals with diagnoses of Learning Disabilities, Mental Health Conditions and Personality Disorder within a pathway of Medium and Low security and the Community&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is based at Westbridge Hostel, a residence in the community run in partnership with Tyne Housing. Westbridge has 12 full time beds and 2 in reach beds; the service is designed to support people with a mental health and offending history as they are discharged from hospital or prison.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will provide occupational assessment and intervention to support transition to the community sustain pro-social occupational roles and routines in the community. You will join a multidisciplinary team at Westbridge and a wider Occupational Therapy service across the Secure Care footprint. You may also be expected to care co-ordinate, take students on placement and provide supervision for junior staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Andrew Parker Team Lead andrew.parker@cntw.nhs.uk 07768541234&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rhona Macleod, Associate Director of AHP/Lead OT on: 0191 246 5261&lt;/p&gt;
